headline: State Street price target lowered to $113 from $118 at Wells Fargo
summary: Wells Fargo lowered the firm’s price target on State Street (STT) to $113 from $118 and keeps an Overweight rating on the shares as part of a Q1 earnings preview for the large-cap banks. The firm is bullish on the sector on a one-year view citing the “biggest deregulation in three decades,” but note that Q1 outlooks “may be tricky” given policy uncertainties.
